# Engineering Operating Model - Planning & Execution Framework

## Purpose

This document summarizes the planning hierarchy, repository organization, and execution model for the Engineering Operating Model (EOM).

The objective is to establish a clear separation between long-term strategy, framework evolution, project execution, and day-to-day engineering work.

---

# Planning Hierarchy

The Engineering Operating Model is organized into five planning levels.

```text
Vision
    │
    ▼
Roadmap (Releases)
    │
    ▼
Milestones
    │
    ▼
Sprints
    │
    ▼
Tasks
```

Each level answers a different question.

| Level     | Purpose                                   | Time Horizon |
| --------- | ----------------------------------------- | ------------ |
| Vision    | Why does the framework exist?             | Years        |
| Roadmap   | What capabilities will be introduced?     | Months       |
| Milestone | What major outcome will be achieved?      | Weeks        |
| Sprint    | What will be delivered next?              | 1-2 Weeks    |
| Task      | What specific work needs to be completed? | Daily        |

