# Enterprise Transformation Phases

These phases apply to transforming an existing software product using the Engineering Operating Model.

## Phase 1

Establish Engineering Confidence

Objective

Understand the current implementation and create a safe foundation for future evolution.

Milestones

* Baseline Freeze
* Implementation Inventory
* Requirements Traceability
* Engineering Safety Net
* Continuous Integration
* Engineering Baseline Report

---

## Phase 2

Establish Engineering Standards

Objective

Standardize engineering practices.

Examples

* Coding standards
* Testing standards
* Documentation standards
* ADR process

---

## Phase 3

Introduce AI-Native Engineering

Objective

Introduce AI agents, skills, and governed workflows.

---

## Phase 4

Continuous Evolution

Objective

Operate the platform using the Engineering Operating Model with ongoing governance and improvement.

