# Engineering Architecture

The framework is organized into three logical layers.

```text
Governance Layer

↓

Orchestration Layer

↓

Execution Layer
```

---

## Governance Layer

Responsible for:

* Policies
* Standards
* Metrics
* Continuous Improvement
* AI Governance
* Repository Governance

Governance observes and improves the operating model rather than participating directly in feature delivery.

---

## Orchestration Layer

Responsible for coordinating engineering activities.

Primary concepts

* Engineering Workflows
* Lifecycle
* Decision Flow

Workflows invoke engineering capabilities in the required sequence.

---

## Execution Layer

The execution hierarchy is:

```text
Persona
    ↓
Capability
    ↓
Agent
    ↓
Skill
    ↓
Artifact
```

---

# Ownership Model

## Persona

Represents an engineering discipline.

Examples

* Product
* Security
* Architecture
* Engineering
* QA
* DevOps
* Governance

---

## Capability

Represents a reusable engineering function.

Examples

* Requirement Analysis
* Threat Modeling
* Architecture Review
* Testing Assessment

Capabilities belong to Personas.

---

## Agent

Represents the executor.

An Agent may be:

* Human Engineer
* AI Assistant
* Automation

Agents execute Skills.

---

## Skill

Represents a repeatable engineering procedure.

Examples

* Implementation Inventory
* Backend Analysis
* API Review
* Traceability Assessment
* Security Assessment
* Engineering Confidence Assessment

Skills produce standardized engineering artifacts.

---

## Artifact

Represents the output produced by a Skill.

Examples

* Specification
* ADR
* Test Plan
* Inventory
* Traceability Matrix
* Engineering Report

Artifacts become inputs to future engineering activities.

---

# Workflow Model

Engineering work is orchestrated through workflows.

Example

```text
Feature Development

↓

Product Capability

↓

Security Capability

↓

Architecture Capability

↓

Engineering Capability

↓

QA Capability

↓

DevOps Capability

↓

Deployment

↑

Governance continuously monitors every stage
```

Workflows orchestrate capabilities.

Capabilities coordinate agents.

Agents execute skills.

Skills produce artifacts.

Governance monitors the entire system.

